 We propose a three-step procedure to guess the restricted TVECM (3). In a first step the two series of 
 prices to be analysed for (combination of different things together that work as one unit) are tested for stationarity, using the increased Dickey-Fuller (ADF) 
 unit root test. After the confirmation of non-stationarity the price series are tested for cointegration using the 
 Johansen method. 
 For comparison reasons and if non-stationarity as well as cointegration can be ended/decided, a linear vector 
 error correction model (1) is guessed in a second step using the error correction term created by the 
