 Johansen method. The number of included falls behind (k) is figured out by/decided by the Akaike information judging requirement (AIC). 
 To guess the more general dividing line vector error correction model (3) we have to decide/figure out the dividing line 
 Î³. For this we use a version of the Hansen and Seo (2001) search procedure10 that depends on the log 
 (thing that decides something) of the guessed error covariance matrix of (3) as the selection judging requirements. The selection judging requirements has 
 the following form: 
 
